RTCStatsReport.summary: The RTCStatsReport interface of the WebRTC API provides a statistics report for a , , or .

remarks.para: An RTCStatsReport instance is a read-only Map-like object, in which each key is an identifier for an object for which statistics are being reported, and the corresponding value is a dictionary object providing the statistics.

RTCStatsReportEntries.summary: The entries() method of the interface returns a new iterator object that can be used to iterate through the key/value pairs for each element in the RTCStatsReport object, in insertion order.

remarks.para: The keys are unique id values for monitored statistics objects from which the statistics are derived, and the associated values are statistics dictionary objects.
The method is otherwise the same as .

RTCStatsReportHas.summary: The has() method of the interface returns a boolean indicating whether a report contains a statistics dictionary with the specified id.

remarks.para: The method is otherwise the same as .

RTCStatsReportHas.returns: true if an element with the specified id exists in the RTCStatsReport object; otherwise false.

RTCStatsReportForEach.summary: The forEach() method of the interface executes a provided function once for each key/value pair in the RTCStatsReport object, in insertion order.

remarks.para: The keys are unique id values for the monitored statistics objects from which the statistics are derived, and the associated values are statistics dictionary objects.
The method is otherwise the same as .

RTCStatsReportSize.summary: The size read-only property of the interface returns the number of items in the current report.

remarks.para: Note that each item consists of a key-value pair, where the keys are unique id values for monitored statistics objects from which the statistics are derived, and the associated values are statistics dictionary objects.
This property is otherwise the same as .

RTCStatsReportSize.value:
An integer indicating the number of items in this report.
The value is zero if the report is empty.

RTCStatsReportGet.summary: The get() method of the interface returns a specified element from an RTCStatsReport.

remarks.para:
Elements in the RTCStatsReport are identified by unique id values, which represent the monitored statistics objects from which the statistics are derived.
The element returned will be an instance of one of the statistics dictionary objects, and it will contain statistics for the object with the given id.
The fetched value is a reference to the statistics dictionary, and any change made to that object will effectively modify it inside the RTCStatsReport object.
The method is otherwise the same as .

RTCStatsReportGet.returns: The element associated with the specified id key, or if the key can't be found in the Map object.

RTCStatsReportKeys.summary: The keys() method of the interface returns a new iterator object that can be used to iterate through the keys for each element in the RTCStatsReport object, in insertion order.

remarks.para: The keys in the RTCStatsReport are unique string id values, which represent the monitored statistics objects from which the statistics are derived.
The method is otherwise the same as .

RTCStatsReportValues.summary: The values() method of the interface returns a new iterator object that can be used to iterate through the values for each element in the RTCStatsReport object, in insertion order.

remarks.para: The values are statistics dictionary objects.
The method is otherwise the same as .

RTCStatsReportSymbol.iterator.summary:
The [Symbol.iterator]() method of the interface implements the iterable protocol and allows statistics reports to be consumed by most syntaxes expecting iterables, such as the spread syntax and loops.
It returns an iterator object that yields the key-value pairs of the report in insertion order.

remarks.para: The initial value of this property is the same function object as the initial value of the method.
The method is otherwise the same as Map.prototype[Symbol.iterator]().

RTCStatsReportSymbol.iterator.returns:
The same return value as .
This is a new iterable iterator object that yields the key-value (id-"statistics dictionary") pairs of the report.
